AGI - "Take the way, at the result of an intense educational work, a common table of the Ministry of Health and the Ministry of the Family, promoted by ministers Orazio Schillaci and Eugenia Roccella, on the problematic of the disforia of genus of minors >, starting from the use of triptorelina, the blocking drug of puberty. The table of technicians and experts, whose composition will be completed in the coming days, is aimed at the elaboration of new specific lines of address, in the light of a reconnaissance of the scientific literature and the experiences of other countries that, after having promoted an extensive practice of these drugs, are reviewing their positions". This is a joint statement by the two ministries, which also summarizes the work done here on the problem of gender dysphoria and the use of blockers.
&nbsp;
"The initiative - we read again in the note - is followed by the hearing, at the Ministry of Health, of the main scientific societies involved in the problem of gender dispersion in adolescents, and to an advanced question to the National Committee of Bioethics to assess the opportunity to review the question of the use of triptorelin in cases of gender dispersion of minors. This application was also accompanied, among other things, by the start of a reconnaissance at the Regions on clinical monitoring and expenditure and triptorelin prescriptions for dysphoria, and the request for a report to AIFA> - the statement concludes - on therapeutic indications for the administration of the drug". &nbsp;

