AGI - The Democratic Party raises a wall against what considers a "political act" of the government against the mayor of Bari Antonio Decaro. Suspect, for the dems, the timing, a few days after the presentation of the lists for the European elections in which Decaro should be deployed, as the serial head of the South constituency. I suspect the chosen target, one of the Pd exponents who can count on a personal consensus patrimony such as to move the fortunes of the vote, in one way or another. In short, there are not only the destinies of Decaro, but the success of the European operation to which the secretary is devoting himself soul and body in these hours. It is on that occasion that political forces will be weighed: with the proportional system and preferences, there are no coalitions that hold. And since the secretary Pd made that appointment the ground on which to challenge Giorgia Meloni, the Bari dossier is at the top of the concerns of the major state Pd.
&nbsp;
Not surprisingly, the news of the Commission's activation, the leader dem put a fire communiqué on the keyboard: "We are based on how Minister Piantedosi announced the appointment of the Commission for the verification of the dissolution of the commune of Bari," writes Schlein: "A choice that, reaching three months from the elections, seems very political, following the initiative of some parliamentarians of the right and two members of the government and having not even examined the documentation submitted by the administration of the mayor Decaro. He had never seen it and it is very serious." The leader has moved all the secretariat dem, from the Head of Local Authorities Davide Baruffi to the Head of Economy, Antonio Misiani, passing by the justice Debora Serracchiani. Reading is unique: it is a political attack. > &nbsp;
&nbsp;
And if political attack must be, they reason parliamentary sources dem, why not negotiate with the same weapons? To do so, it is explained, Decaro could resign as mayor thus obtaining two immediate results. The step back, in fact, would have the effect of defuse the impact on the image of the exponent Pd; It would allow Decaro to show his desire to prioritize the honourability of his Junta and the city of Bari to any personal interest. A hypothesis, for the moment, that emerges from the pourparlers of the Transatlantic. The Nazareno line, in fact, remains that of solidarity and full support for its mayor, along with the attack on the choice of Minister Piantedosi. To scan parliamentary sources dem, the demand emerges to the greater state of a "strong initiative to respond to the manganellata of Piantedosi>".
&nbsp;
It is not enough, I mean, "posts and declarations of solidarity, we need a step forward," it is explained. Despite this, there are those who ask to keep in mind that, whether we like it or not, there is an ongoing investigation of which we must wait for conclusions. "We are confident that the results will highlight the correctness of the Decaro administration but remains the absurd institutional ruthlessness brought forward by the right for mere electoral calculations." In particular, the first citizens are confronted with what they consider as an instrumental and political use of the powers of Viminale: "Very bad what is happening in Bari. Solidarity with the mayor Antonio Decaro, always at the forefront of legality >", says the mayor of Rome Roberto Gualtieri: "An unacceptable political and instrumental use of the powers that the law assigns to the government, which is a dangerous precedent", adds Gualtieri.&nbsp; "As Italian mayors we are very shocked by the news," says the mayor of Bologna Matteo Lepore: "As well as all colleagues, we are expressing maximum solidarity to the president of Anci, to the mayor of Bari, who is a person we know, of great moral stature. This intervention by the tight-leged government, a few months after the elections in Bari, is very suspicious. Like so many other things that this government does." &nbsp;

